data.title: Port Louis, Mauritius
data.meta_description:
The capital City of the island, and where all the big freighters that bring take produce to and from the island come, thus it's name. It's also a City ( small town to us in UK) full of colour and life it you venture towards the spice markets and soak up the atmosphere and smells of fresh hers being chopped and spices sold in mass. quantities. 
	Summer holiday 2013 - we visited just for 2 and half hours one Saturday morning, as very busy with the commute Mon-Friday certain hours.
